<subSubSection id="C328ABCEFFB148007BB0FB29FB524A91" pageId="12" pageNumber="120" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8DF845FFB148007BB0FB29FE954A0B" blockId="12.[189,310,1273,1299]" box="[189,310,1273,1299]" pageId="12" pageNumber="120">
<heading id="D0C54F29FFB148007BB0FB29FE954A0B" bold="true" box="[189,310,1273,1299]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="12" pageNumber="120" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFB148007BB0FB29FE954A0B" bold="true" box="[189,310,1273,1299]" pageId="12" pageNumber="120">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8DF845FFB148007BB0FAF8FB524A91" blockId="12.[189,1399,1320,1417]" pageId="12" pageNumber="120">
Species with strongly horizontal carinae in mesoscutum and notauli. Morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFB148007BB0FA9CFED24A7D" authorityName="Fergusson" authorityYear="1985" box="[189,369,1356,1382]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aegilips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="romseyensis">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFB148007BB0FA9CFED24A7D" box="[189,369,1356,1382]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="120">A. romseyensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it can be distinguished by having horizontal carinate sculpture in the mesoscutum and areolate scutellum (mesoscutum and scutellum smooth in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFB148007F3CFABFFB7C4A90" authorityName="Fergusson" authorityYear="1985" box="[1073,1247,1391,1417]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aegilips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="romseyensis">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFB148007F3CFABFFB7C4A90" box="[1073,1247,1391,1417]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="120">A. romseyensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
